===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} {{term|scyrte|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem}} ''*skurtijon''.  Cognate with Dutch {{term|schort|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Schürze||apron|lang=de}}.  {{term|skirt|Skirt|lang=en}} is a parallel formation from Old Norse; compare also {{term|short|lang=en}}, from the same ultimate source.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-shirt.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: {{rhymes|ɜː(r)t}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An [[article]] of [[clothing]] that is [[wear|worn]] on the upper part of the [[body]], and often has [[sleeve]]s, either long or short, that cover the arms.
# In "[[shirts and skins]]" games, a member of the shirt-wearing team.

